---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Home | UXplore">
	<header class="page-header">
		<p class="section-label">Welcome</p>
		<h1>UXplore</h1>
		<p class="lead">
			A virtual classroom where you guide your learning with our resources—synchronous or asynchronous.
		</p>
	</header>

	<div class="card home-welcome">
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				Welcome to <strong>UXplore</strong>, a virtual classroom where you can guide your learning using our
				resources whether it be synchronous or asynchronous. Our mission is to make your education journey
				effortless and engaging. We offer online classes, video tutorials, and hands-on opportunities to learn
				and test your knowledge.
			</p>
			<p>
				If you are a first-year student looking to enrich your UX abilities—good news: you're in the right place!
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<section class="card home-section" aria-labelledby="getting-started-heading">
		<h2 id="getting-started-heading">Getting Started</h2>
		<p>
			To begin or continue your journey, start by clicking your preferred choice of learning—either
			asynchronous or synchronous.
		</p>

		<p class="home-section__question">Unsure where to go?</p>

		<div class="home-explainers">
			<div class="home-explainer home-explainer--teal">
				<span class="home-explainer__label">Asynchronous</span>
				<p>
					If you prefer to work on your own time with no face-to-face interaction, we have the perfect page for you.
					Learn through posted videos, then complete the quiz to test your knowledge and identify where you can
					improve. You can select the UX topic that interests you most or that you haven't completed yet.
				</p>
				<a class="home-explainer__link" href="/asynchronous">Go to Asynchronous →</a>
			</div>
			<div class="home-explainer home-explainer--violet">
				<span class="home-explainer__label">Synchronous</span>
				<p>
					If you prefer to learn by speaking in real time with an educator, visit the synchronous page where you
					can join a live class via Zoom and participate in activities led in class.
				</p>
				<a class="home-explainer__link" href="/synchronous">Go to Synchronous →</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="home-section__question">Still have questions about content?</p>
		<p>
			Visit the <a href="/discussion">Discussion Board</a> where you can communicate and ask questions,
			share comments, or opinions related to the course. If you feel confident in your knowledge, feel
			free to reply to others. By communicating freely with fellow students we can build a UX learning
			community together!
		</p>

		<p class="home-section__question">Take your experience one step further</p>
		<p>
			To test yourself and apply your learning, UXplore is offering a chance to compete and learn
			alongside others in a virtual case competition. Visit the <a href="/case-study">Case Study</a> page
			to see instructions, a preview of the upcoming challenge, and to sign up yourself and your team
			members.
		</p>

		<p class="home-cta-lead">
			Begin your learning experience by clicking the button of your choice below, or use the navigation menu at the top of every page!
		</p>
	</section>

	<nav class="home-nav-grid" aria-label="Main sections">
		<a class="home-nav__btn home-nav__btn--teal" href="/asynchronous">
			<span class="home-nav__title">Asynchronous</span>
			<span class="home-nav__desc">Video modules &amp; quizzes — learn at your own pace</span>
		</a>
		<a class="home-nav__btn home-nav__btn--violet" href="/synchronous">
			<span class="home-nav__title">Synchronous</span>
			<span class="home-nav__desc">Live Zoom sessions &amp; in-class activities</span>
		</a>
		<a class="home-nav__btn home-nav__btn--sky" href="/discussion">
			<span class="home-nav__title">Discussion Board</span>
			<span class="home-nav__desc">Ask questions &amp; connect with classmates</span>
		</a>
		<a class="home-nav__btn home-nav__btn--amber" href="/case-study">
			<span class="home-nav__title">Case Study</span>
			<span class="home-nav__desc">Virtual case competition &amp; challenge</span>
		</a>
	</nav>
</Layout>

<style>
	.home-welcome {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.home-section {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.home-section h2 {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	.home-section p {
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		max-width: 52rem;
	}

	.home-section a {
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 500;
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.home-section a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	.home-section__question {
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: var(--text);
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem !important;
	}

	.home-explainers {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.home-explainers { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}

	.home-explainer {
		border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
		padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}

	.home-explainer--teal {
		background: var(--accent-soft);
		border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
	}

	.home-explainer--violet {
		background: #ede9fe;
		border-left: 4px solid #7c3aed;
	}

	.home-explainer__label {
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.home-explainer p {
		margin: 0 !important;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--muted);
	}

	.home-explainer__link {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: none;
		margin-top: 0.25rem;
	}

	.home-explainer--violet .home-explainer__link {
		color: #7c3aed;
	}

	.home-explainer__link:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	.home-cta-lead {
		margin-top: 1.75rem !important;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		margin-bottom: 0 !important;
	}

	.home-nav-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 540px) {
		.home-nav-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
</style>